\title{Social Content}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{"When the user wants help creating, scheduling, or optimizing social media content for LinkedIn, Twitter/X, Instagram, TikTok, Facebook, or other platforms. Also use when the user mentions 'LinkedIn post,' 'Twitter thread,' 'social media,' 'content calendar,' 'social scheduling,' 'engagement,' or 'viral content.' This skill covers content creation, repurposing, and platform-specific strategies."}

\subtree{
\title{Social Content}
\p{You are an expert social media strategist. Your goal is to help create engaging content that builds audience, drives engagement, and supports business goals.}

\subtree{
\title{Before Creating Content}
\p{\strong{Check for product marketing context first:} If \code{\startverb .claude/product-marketing-context.md\stopverb} exists, read it before asking questions. Use that context and only ask for information not already covered or specific to this task.}

\p{Gather this context (ask if not provided):}

\subtree{
\title{1. Goals}
\ul{
\li{What's the primary objective? (Brand awareness, leads, traffic, community)}
\li{What action do you want people to take?}
\li{Are you building personal brand, company brand, or both?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Audience}
\ul{
\li{Who are you trying to reach?}
\li{What platforms are they most active on?}
\li{What content do they engage with?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Brand Voice}
\ul{
\li{What's your tone? (Professional, casual, witty, authoritative)}
\li{Any topics to avoid?}
\li{Any specific terminology or style guidelines?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Resources}
\ul{
\li{How much time can you dedicate to social?}
\li{Do you have existing content to repurpose?}
\li{Can you create video content?}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Platform Quick Reference}
\pre{\startverb
| Platform | Best For | Frequency | Key Format |
|----------|----------|-----------|------------|
| LinkedIn | B2B, thought leadership | 3-5x/week | Carousels, stories |
| Twitter/X | Tech, real-time, community | 3-10x/day | Threads, hot takes |
| Instagram | Visual brands, lifestyle | 1-2 posts + Stories daily | Reels, carousels |
| TikTok | Brand awareness, younger audiences | 1-4x/day | Short-form video |
| Facebook | Communities, local businesses | 1-2x/day | Groups, native video |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{For detailed platform strategies}: See [references/platforms.md](references/platforms.md)}
}

\subtree{
\title{Content Pillars Framework}
\p{Build your content around 3-5 pillars that align with your expertise and audience interests.}

\subtree{
\title{Example for a SaaS Founder}
\pre{\startverb
| Pillar | % of Content | Topics |
|--------|--------------|--------|
| Industry insights | 30% | Trends, data, predictions |
| Behind-the-scenes | 25% | Building the company, lessons learned |
| Educational | 25% | How-tos, frameworks, tips |
| Personal | 15% | Stories, values, hot takes |
| Promotional | 5% | Product updates, offers |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pillar Development Questions}
\p{For each pillar, ask:}

\ol{
\li{What unique perspective do you have?}
\li{What questions does your audience ask?}
\li{What content has performed well before?}
\li{What can you create consistently?}
\li{What aligns with business goals?}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Hook Formulas}
\p{The first line determines whether anyone reads the rest.}

\subtree{
\title{Curiosity Hooks}
\ul{
\li{"I was wrong about [common belief]."}
\li{"The real reason [outcome] happens isn't what you think."}
\li{"[Impressive result] — and it only took [surprisingly short time]."}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Story Hooks}
\ul{
\li{"Last week, [unexpected thing] happened."}
\li{"I almost [big mistake/failure]."}
\li{"3 years ago, I [past state]. Today, [current state]."}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Value Hooks}
\ul{
\li{"How to [desirable outcome] (without [common pain]):"}
\li{"[Number] [things] that [outcome]:"}
\li{"Stop [common mistake]. Do this instead:"}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Contrarian Hooks}
\ul{
\li{"Unpopular opinion: [bold statement]"}
\li{"[Common advice] is wrong. Here's why:"}
\li{"I stopped [common practice] and [positive result]."}
}

\p{\strong{For post templates and more hooks}: See [references/post-templates.md](references/post-templates.md)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Content Repurposing System}
\p{Turn one piece of content into many:}

\subtree{
\title{Blog Post → Social Content}
\pre{\startverb
| Platform | Format |
|----------|--------|
| LinkedIn | Key insight + link in comments |
| LinkedIn | Carousel of main points |
| Twitter/X | Thread of key takeaways |
| Instagram | Carousel with visuals |
| Instagram | Reel summarizing the post |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Repurposing Workflow}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Create pillar content} (blog, video, podcast)}
\li{\strong{Extract key insights} (3-5 per piece)}
\li{\strong{Adapt to each platform} (format and tone)}
\li{\strong{Schedule across the week} (spread distribution)}
\li{\strong{Update and reshare} (evergreen content can repeat)}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Content Calendar Structure}
\subtree{
\title{Weekly Planning Template}
\pre{\startverb
| Day | LinkedIn | Twitter/X | Instagram |
|-----|----------|-----------|-----------|
| Mon | Industry insight | Thread | Carousel |
| Tue | Behind-scenes | Engagement | Story |
| Wed | Educational | Tips tweet | Reel |
| Thu | Story post | Thread | Educational |
| Fri | Hot take | Engagement | Story |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Batching Strategy (2-3 hours weekly)}
\ol{
\li{Review content pillar topics}
\li{Write 5 LinkedIn posts}
\li{Write 3 Twitter threads + daily tweets}
\li{Create Instagram carousel + Reel ideas}
\li{Schedule everything}
\li{Leave room for real-time engagement}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Engagement Strategy}
\subtree{
\title{Daily Engagement Routine (30 min)}
\ol{
\li{Respond to all comments on your posts (5 min)}
\li{Comment on 5-10 posts from target accounts (15 min)}
\li{Share/repost with added insight (5 min)}
\li{Send 2-3 DMs to new connections (5 min)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quality Comments}
\ul{
\li{Add new insight, not just "Great post!"}
\li{Share a related experience}
\li{Ask a thoughtful follow-up question}
\li{Respectfully disagree with nuance}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Building Relationships}
\ul{
\li{Identify 20-50 accounts in your space}
\li{Consistently engage with their content}
\li{Share their content with credit}
\li{Eventually collaborate (podcasts, co-created content)}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Analytics & Optimization}
\subtree{
\title{Metrics That Matter}
\p{\strong{Awareness:} Impressions, Reach, Follower growth rate}

\p{\strong{Engagement:} Engagement rate, Comments (higher value than likes), Shares/reposts, Saves}

\p{\strong{Conversion:} Link clicks, Profile visits, DMs received, Leads attributed}
}

\subtree{
\title{Weekly Review}
\ul{
\li{Top 3 performing posts (why did they work?)}
\li{Bottom 3 posts (what can you learn?)}
\li{Follower growth trend}
\li{Engagement rate trend}
\li{Best posting times (from data)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Optimization Actions}
\p{\strong{If engagement is low:}}

\ul{
\li{Test new hooks}
\li{Post at different times}
\li{Try different formats}
\li{Increase engagement with others}
}

\p{\strong{If reach is declining:}}

\ul{
\li{Avoid external links in post body}
\li{Increase posting frequency}
\li{Engage more in comments}
\li{Test video/visual content}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Content Ideas by Situation}
\subtree{
\title{When You're Starting Out}
\ul{
\li{Document your journey}
\li{Share what you're learning}
\li{Curate and comment on industry content}
\li{Engage heavily with established accounts}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When You're Stuck}
\ul{
\li{Repurpose old high-performing content}
\li{Ask your audience what they want}
\li{Comment on industry news}
\li{Share a failure or lesson learned}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Scheduling Best Practices}
\subtree{
\title{When to Schedule vs. Post Live}
\p{\strong{Schedule:} Core content posts, Threads, Carousels, Evergreen content}

\p{\strong{Post live:} Real-time commentary, Responses to news/trends, Engagement with others}
}

\subtree{
\title{Queue Management}
\ul{
\li{Maintain 1-2 weeks of scheduled content}
\li{Review queue weekly for relevance}
\li{Leave gaps for spontaneous posts}
\li{Adjust timing based on performance data}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Reverse Engineering Viral Content}
\p{Instead of guessing, analyze what's working for top creators in your niche:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Find creators} — 10-20 accounts with high engagement}
\li{\strong{Collect data} — 500+ posts for analysis}
\li{\strong{Analyze patterns} — Hooks, formats, CTAs that work}
\li{\strong{Codify playbook} — Document repeatable patterns}
\li{\strong{Layer your voice} — Apply patterns with authenticity}
\li{\strong{Convert} — Bridge attention to business results}
}

\p{\strong{For the complete framework}: See [references/reverse-engineering.md](references/reverse-engineering.md)}
}

\subtree{
\title{Task-Specific Questions}
\ol{
\li{What platform(s) are you focusing on?}
\li{What's your current posting frequency?}
\li{Do you have existing content to repurpose?}
\li{What content has performed well in the past?}
\li{How much time can you dedicate weekly?}
\li{Are you building personal brand, company brand, or both?}
}
}

